en.expected_results:
PORTOS establishes the following instruments:
1. The open platform BLUE-PORTS established to promote energy self-sufficiency in ports of the Atlantic Area through Marine Renewable Energies (MRE). A stable network of cooperation is created to share information regarding emerging MRE technologies, relevant news in the sector and technical suppliers at the different links in the value chain of MRE;
3. The OpenPorts and OpenLabs days will maintain the link with society and its involvement on the development of offshore renewable energies and the adoption of self-sufficiency practices;
5. Engagement and commitment of Port Associations to promote development of environmental policies in Atlantic Area ports, encouraging RE/MRE implementation to allow set environmental goals to be met;
6. A specific social perception plan created to show the opportunities that MRE brings to the Atlantic Area regions and to involve the main actors (staff from enterprises, public bodies and independent developers) in the development projects.

en.expected_outputs:
• Detailed energy efficiency audit of three case-study ports;
• MRE exploitation plans and pilot actions for each case-study, including the most adequate MRE mix and conversion technologies;
• Roadmap and guidelines to reach energy self-sufficiency in the AA port system;
• Demonstrators of three hybrid technologies to enable exploitation of RE/MRE resources in case-study ports;
• Decision Support System for implementing RE/MRE technologies in AA ports;
• Proofs of concept of cutting edge technologies;
• Actions (Open days/Open Labs) to involve society in the development of marine renewable energies;
• Training and know-how transference to key-stakeholders, end users and society.

• 1 pilot implemented in 4 partner regions; 
•  2 technical research publications on ‘Using technology measure the impact of investing in trails’,
‘Developing virtual trail tourism in AA regions’, 5 case studies on economic value of trails in AA regions; 
•  1 ‘trail dashboard’ visualising real time trail metrics, 2 trail apps on enhancing virtual trail experiences & developing asset management tools, 5 bespoke destination management plans,•  5000 online audiences & visitors in the 4 regions;
